How can we sample p?
1. Bad strategy: rejection sampling by doing random walks and reject
non-self-avoiding walks. Very ecient because the rejection rate is high
(i.e. paths are more likely to cross themselves than not). Very easy to
simulate though. At every time step, just ip a four-sided coin.
2. To generate self-avoiding walk, at every time step choose uniformly among
the unvisited neighbouring nodes a node to move to. If there no such
unvisited neighbors before length m walk is achieved, then we need to
start over. The problem with this method is that the self-avoiding walk
produced by this algorithm is not uniformly distributed.
